cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing and specifically the demosaicing problem. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The evaluation of the proposed models on popular benchmarks suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of different color filter arrays (CFAs) and the joint optimization of the CFA design and demosaicing method suggest that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
